_pdbx_database_remark.id     700 
_pdbx_database_remark.text   
;SHEET
THERE ARE SEVERAL SUBTLE ASPECTS OF THE SECONDARY STRUCTURE
OF THIS MOLECULE WHICH CANNOT CONVENIENTLY BE REPRESENTED
IN THE HELIX AND SHEET RECORDS BELOW.  THESE ASPECTS
INFLUENCE THE REPRESENTATION OF HELIX 6 AND STRAND 3 OF
SHEET *S1*.  THE PAPER CITED AS REFERENCE 26 ABOVE SHOULD
BE CONSULTED FOR THESE SUBTLETIES.
;
# 
_pdbx_entry_details.entry_id                 1L42 
_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details         
;IN THIS MUTANT STRUCTURE THE SIDE CHAIN OF GLU 16 APPEARS
TO HAVE TWO DIFFERENT CONFORMATIONS.  THE STRUCTURE WAS
REFINED WITH THE SIDE CHAIN IN THE TWO ALTERNATIVE
CONFORMATIONS.  PROTEIN DATA BANK ENTRIES 1L42 AND 1L43
CONTAIN COORDINATES CORRESPONDING TO THE TWO DIFFERENT
CONFORMATIONS OF GLU 16.
;
